      "question": "A fraud examiner is analyzing the behavioral patterns of a suspected fraudster who has been systematically manipulating vendor invoices over a three-year period. The individual shows no remorse when confronted, demonstrates sophisticated planning abilities, and has a history of violating company policies without regard for consequences. Which behavioral characteristic is MOST indicative of this individual's criminal mindset?",
